text:
The Senate Judiciary Committee on Wednesday made public more than 2,500 pages of testimony, notes and statements from the people who attended a much scrutinized Trump Tower meeting in June 2016.
Here is a rundown of the people at the meeting, which was set up after Donald Trump Jr. was promised incriminating information on Democratic presidential candidate Hillary Clinton provided by Russia. No such information was provided, according to the attendees.
